    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A journalist is analyzing a collection of quotes from different sources and needs to check if any quotes appear more than once.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">Article</code> class, write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">hasDuplicateQuotes()</code> to return <code>true</code> if any quote in the list appears more than once, and <code>false</code> otherwise.\r\n1. Loop through the list of quotes to get the first quote.\r\n\r\n2. Loop through the list again to compare it with every other quote.\r\n\t- If a duplicate is found, return true.\r\n\r\n3. If no duplicates are found, return false.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">ArticleRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">hasDuplicateQuotes()</code> method and print whether duplicate quotes exist.\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;\">🔦 Need help with your algorithm?</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    \t<p>Here is one approach to solving this problem.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nLoop through the list of quotes to get the first quote\r\n   Loop through the list of quotes to get the second quote\r\n   \tIf the first quote matches the second quote\r\n    \t\treturn true\r\nReturn false\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>",
